Describe something you did that made you feel proud
- what it was
- how you did it
- how difficult it was
- explain why you felt proud of it

I’d like to talk about a time when I felt really proud of myself, which was when I prepared for and passed the national entrance examination. This happened during my final year of high school, which was one of the most challenging periods in my life.

At that time, I had to prepare for a very important exam that would determine whether I could get into my dream university. The preparation process was quite demanding, as I had to absorb a large amount of knowledge across various subjects, including both scientific and social ones. On top of that, the competition was intense, which added a lot of pressure.

To deal with this, I took a systematic approach. Besides attending regular classes at school, I also enrolled in extra classes to strengthen my understanding. I often studied with my friends, which helped me stay motivated and improve more quickly. Whenever I had difficulties, I didn’t hesitate to ask my teachers for guidance, and they were always supportive.

There were times when I felt overwhelmed by the workload, so I tried to manage my stress by going swimming. Being in the water really helped me relax and clear my mind, which allowed me to stay focused in the long run.

In the end, all my efforts paid off. I achieved a high score in the exam and was accepted into a prestigious university specializing in Information Technology. My parents were extremely proud of me and even bought me a laptop to support my studies.

Looking back, I feel proud not only because of the result but also because of my persistence and discipline throughout the process. I believe these qualities will continue to benefit me in the future.
